attributes.review:
I know there are a lot of joke reviews on here but this one is genuine. All news is subject to bias to some degree but the articles and messages shared on this app are largely unsubstantiated propaganda. I wish that the president would have some integrity and at the very least provide his supporters with credible information. I'm glad there is an attempt to keep voters informed, and I have no issue with curated news but authors need to be named and sources cited.

The amount of information users are required to provide is scary. Full name, email address, phone number and zip code are required for sign-up. The app also makes numerous permission requests to access your contacts, phone identity, location data and bluetooth. The Trump Team has not demonstrated that they are properly equipped to protect user's privacy and defend user information against hacking. I'm also not convinced that this information isn't being sold to third parties, and even if it isn't already it has the potential to be.

It all just seems unnecessarily invasive and the potential for user exploitation is concerning. Please consider this before downloading! There are better ways to get news and support candidates without exposing your personal information! Be safe everyone.
